## Activation

**Keywords:** "Implement frontend", "Code UI", "Frontend development", "After design approval"

**Prerequisites:**
- ✅ Product-Designer completed
- ✅ User approved design
- ✅ Engineering Doc ready (FE section)

---

## Role & Responsibilities

### Input
- Master Doc: `Docs/00-master/<feature>-<ticket>_master_*.md`
- Engineering Doc: `Docs/02-engineering/<feature>-<ticket>_engineering_*.md` (FE section)
- Design Artifacts: `Docs/01-product/mockups/`
- Approved wireframes and mockups

### Tasks
1. Read all documentation
2. Review design mockups
3. Implement frontend components (React/TSX)
4. Follow `frontend-code-standards` skill
5. Apply `Review-clean-code` workflow before commit
6. Update Engineering Doc (FE section) with changelog
7. Create PR with proper changelog (base → test)
8. Report to Thread 727

### Tools Used
- **QwenCLI** — Code implementation
- **frontend-code-standards** skill — Code conventions
- **Review-clean-code** skill — Clean code & commit
- **shadcn/ui** — Component library
- **Tailwind CSS** — Styling

### Output Artifacts
- Frontend components
- Updated Engineering Doc (FE section)
- PR with changelog (→ test branch)

---

## Workflow

```
Step 1: Read Requirements & Design
  → Master Doc + Engineering Doc (FE section) + Design mockups

Step 2: Setup & Planning
  → Task breakdown
  → Identify components to create/modify
  → Check existing codebase for patterns

Step 3: Implementation
  → Import order: React → third-party → @/ → relative
  → Component structure: Interface → hooks → handlers → JSX
  → API via services/ only (no raw fetch in UI)
  → TypeScript types (no any)
  → Tailwind + cn() for styling
  → i18n: all text from t() — NO hardcoded strings

Step 4: Clean Code Review (Before Commit)
  → Remove all console.* calls
  → Check for hard-coded values
  → Verify import order
  → Run TypeScript check
  → Run lint
  → Run build

Step 5: Commit → Follow commit-and-pr-rules
Step 6: Create PR (→ test branch)
Step 7: Report to Thread 727
```

